The paper deals with algorithms for analyzing graphs with differential privacy, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The privacy aspect of the paper also suggests it could be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of approximation algorithms and analysis of error bounds suggests it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
